{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3319292,"name":"","username":"mjjain","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/7cd45c/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-02-27T23:50:38.267Z","cooked":"<p>Does anyone know why sometimes the getDistance() method for REV Thrubore’s is inconcistent?</p>
<p>Im using the duty cycle class and doing the following to convert to degrees.</p>
<p>thruBore.setPositionOffset(0.659); (offset parallel to ground)<br>
thruBore.setDistancePerRotation(-360);</p>
<p>Usually, it works when I call the getDistance() method. If the arm is at -90 degrees, it will usually report that. But sometimes when I redeoply, it switches to 270 (the long way). It’s kind of random? Sometimes if I powercycle it the encoder will report 270 and other times it will report -90 without moving anything. Any ideas?</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2024-02-27T23:51:24.424Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":97,"readers_count":96,"score":34.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":456433,"topic_slug":"rev-thrubore-encoder-conversions-not-always-staying","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":51252,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/rev-thrubore-encoder-conversions-not-always-staying/456433/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3319469,"name":"","username":"mjjain","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/7cd45c/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-02-28T04:32:51.804Z","cooked":"<p>It’s worth noting that sometimes between power cycles and deploys it works totally fine and maintains the proper reading. It’s just unpredictable it seems unless I’m missing smth.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2024-02-28T04:32:51.804Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":85,"readers_count":84,"score":22.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":456433,"topic_slug":"rev-thrubore-encoder-conversions-not-always-staying","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":51252,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/rev-thrubore-encoder-conversions-not-always-staying/456433/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3333201,"name":"loafdog","username":"loafdog","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/l/df788c/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-03-14T18:59:04.522Z","cooked":"<p>We just started seeing the same thing on our competition bot last night.  First time we have seen it happen after weeks of using the encoder on our practice bot arm.  Our comp bot we have been using for about a week or so.  One thing we want to try is swapping the encoder for new one to see if problem persists.  <a class="mention" href="/u/mjjain">@mjjain</a> did you ever solve this issue?</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2024-03-14T18:59:04.522Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":53,"readers_count":52,"score":15.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":456433,"topic_slug":"rev-thrubore-encoder-conversions-not-always-staying","display_username":"loafdog","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":51252,"username":"mjjain","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/7cd45c/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":11178,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/rev-thrubore-encoder-conversions-not-always-staying/456433/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3340990,"name":"","username":"mjjain","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/7cd45c/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-03-22T22:48:28.705Z","cooked":"<p>Yeah we did. Ended up just using the absolute position and applying our conversion factor in a separate method. Looks something like this:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public double getAbsoluteShooterTiltPosRaw() {
        return shooterTiltThruBoreEncoder.getAbsolutePosition();
    }

public double getAbsoluteShooterTiltPosDegrees() {
        return -Units.rotationsToDegrees(getAbsoluteShooterTiltPosRaw() - ShooterConstants.TILT_OFFSET);
    }

We use the getAbsoluteShooterTiltPosDegrees() method whenever we need to access the value in degrees, and it's been working perfectly!
